name: Warren County Health
tweet: Throw out perishable food that has been sitting at room temperature for more than 2 hours (more than 1 hour if it has been exposed to temperatures above 90°F). Stay food safe AND enjoy the game!  https://t.co/nQHVcfXFwp

name: Warren County Health
tweet: Keep hot foods hot (140°F or warmer) and cold foods cold (40°F or colder). Reminder for Food Safety Education Month!  https://t.co/DngAcJI48H

name: Warren County Health
tweet: Separate raw meats from ready-to-eat foods like vegetables when preparing, serving, or storing foods. Make sure food is cooked to a safe internal temperature.  https://t.co/flh3HwUQlR

name: Warren County Health
tweet: It's Food Safety Education Month! Wash your hands with soap and running water for at least 20 seconds before, during, and after preparing food and before eating.  https://t.co/uiSImyE4Y1
